A7-Network Graph Assignment

11/6/2020

# reference (https://jokergoo.github.io/circlize_book/book/advanced-usage-of-chorddiagram.html#fig:chord-diagram-default-track)
# import lib
library(tidyr)
library(dplyr)
library(data.table)
library(tibble)
library(circlize)

header=readxl::read_excel("State_to_State_Migrations_Table_2018.xls",skip = 4,n_max=3, col_names = FALSE) 
# reshape the header df and filter the useful col 
header= data.frame(t(rbind(header, colnames(header)))) %>% 
        filter(X3  == "Estimate" &  !is.na(X2))%>% 
        slice(c(2:52,54))

# get useful col number 
col = header   %>% .$X4 %>%as.vector
col = append(col,"...1",0)
# load the full data
df=readxl::read_excel("State_to_State_Migrations_Table_2018.xls",skip = 4,col_names = FALSE)

df = df %>% select(col)%>%
           # rename cols 
            setnames(old = as.vector(header$X4), as.vector( header$X2)) %>%
           # filter out the empty rows
            drop_na("...1") %>%
           # drop the useless rows 
            filter( ...1 != "Current residence in")%>%
          # remove the Footnotes
            slice(2:53) %>%
           # add row name - covert col to row names
            column_to_rownames('...1')

# get the new data frame with 3 columns: source, target and count
df2 = data.frame(reshape2::melt(as.matrix(df), value.name = "count", varnames=c('target', 'source')))
# convert na to 0
df2[df2 == "N/A"] = 0
# correct data type
df2$count = as.numeric(as.character(df2$count))
# select New York, Texas and two other states as the origin states
df3 = df2[df2$source %in% c("New York","Texas","Colorado","Wisconsin"),]

# top 10 destination states
df4 = tibble::as_tibble(df3) %>%
  group_by(source) %>%
  arrange(count, .by_group = TRUE) %>%
  top_n(10)

# convert state name to abbr
df4$target = state.abb[match(df4$target, state.name)]
df4$source = state.abb[match(df4$source, state.name)]
# re-order the cols
df4 = df4[,c("source","target","count")]
#'New York', "Texas", "Colorado" , "Wisconsin"
circos.clear()
chordDiagram(df4,  annotationTrack = c("name", "grid"),
             # re-order the graph
             order = c('NY', "TX", "CO" , "WI","NC","WY","WA", "MN","AZ","MI","FL","MO","CA","SC","VA","MA","CT","IA","PA", "TN","NJ","AR","GA","LA","OK","IN","IL","NM"),
             # assign color
             grid.col = c(NY="#F8B195", TX="#F67280",CO="#6C5B7B", WI="#355C7D",NC="lightgrey",WY="lightgrey",WA="lightgrey",AZ="lightgrey",FL="lightgrey",MO="lightgrey",CA="lightgrey",SC="lightgrey",VA="lightgrey",MA="lightgrey",CT="lightgrey",PA="lightgrey",TN="lightgrey",NJ="lightgrey",AR="lightgrey",GA="lightgrey",LA="lightgrey",OK="lightgrey",IN="lightgrey",MI="lightgrey",IA="lightgrey",IL="lightgrey",MN="lightgrey",NM="lightgrey"),
             annotationTrackHeight = c(0.03, 0.01),transparency = 0.2,big.gap = 1)
title("Migrations Network of NY,TX,CO,WI", cex = 0.6)
